Second test: Compiling and Running and Application that falls back to OpenGL 2.1 when opening and achieving an OpenGL 3.0 context is not possible. Since the error message hinted at version and extension, we tried two things at once: produce OpenGL code that does not employ GLUT (even if this won't be feasible later for educational purposes - but it is a form to test if OpenGL runs) produce OpenGLÂ  code that does not rely on the possibility of cretaing an OpenGL 3.0 context, but rather has the ability to fall back to an earlier version). We tested the code first on a barebones Linux distribution with the minimu infrastructure and it did run. It did also compile on the VPL server. It did not run on the VPL server. The error message, however, was different this time: 
```text
Invalid GLX version
```
